.TH "ntb_msi_peer_addr" 9 "ntb_msi_peer_addr" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ntb_msi_peer_addr \- Get the DMA address to trigger a peer's MSI interrupt
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" ntb_msi_peer_addr
.BI "(struct ntb_dev *ntb "  ","
.BI "int peer "  ","
.BI "struct ntb_msi_desc *desc "  ","
.BI "phys_addr_t *msi_addr "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ntb" 12
NTB device context
.IP "peer" 12
Peer index
.IP "desc" 12
MSI descriptor data which triggers the interrupt
.IP "msi_addr" 12
Physical address to trigger the interrupt
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function allows using DMA engines to trigger an interrupt
(for example, trigger an interrupt to process the data after
sending it). To trigger the interrupt, write \fIdesc.data\fP to the address
returned in \fImsi_addr\fP
.SH "RETURN"
Zero on success, otherwise a negative error number.
